            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Three arrays of detectors were used. Two arrays of",
                "three square silicon pindiode detectors with active",
                "area of 18*18 mm**2 and thickness of 500 mum covered",
                "laboratory angles 4.2-19.3 degree. These were used as",
                "alpha-particle detectors.",
                "A delta-E-E telescope covered the laboratory angles",
                "4.75-11.8 degree. The telescope consisted of a gas",
                "ionization chamber filled with P-10 gas and a position",
                "sensitive silicon detector (resistive layer). The",
                "active area of the telescope was determined by a",
                "collimator 45.9 mm long and 2 mm wide. The delta E-E",
                "telescope was used to identify and measure the position",
                "and energies of the Li-6 recoils."
              ]
            }
          ],
